461
00:50:01,747 --> 00:50:05,524
Indeed, Monsieur Mélies
believed so himself.

462
00:50:05,651 --> 00:50:07,562
But we began a search.

463
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:11,133
We looked through vaults,
through private collections,

464
00:50:11,290 --> 00:50:14,760
barns and catacombs.

465
00:50:15,461 --> 00:50:18,635
Our work was rewarded
with old negatives,

466
00:50:18,797 --> 00:50:23,746
boxes of prints, and trunks
full of decaying film,

467
00:50:23,902 --> 00:50:26,109
which we were able to save.

468
00:50:26,272 --> 00:50:30,220
We now have over 80 films
by Georges Méliés.

469
00:50:35,948 --> 00:50:38,986
And tonight, their creator,

470
00:50:39,151 --> 00:50:42,928
and the newest member
of the Film Academy faculty,

471
00:50:43,088 --> 00:50:45,932
is here to share them with you.

472
00:51:01,840 --> 00:51:03,751
Bravo!

473
00:51:08,814 --> 00:51:09,849
Bravo!

474
00:51:21,126 --> 00:51:22,935
Ladies and gentlemen...

475
00:51:24,630 --> 00:51:26,166
I...

476
00:51:35,674 --> 00:51:38,814
I am standing before you tonight...

477
00:51:40,312 --> 00:51:43,452
because of one
very brave young man...

478
00:51:46,385 --> 00:51:51,391
who saw a broken machine...

479
00:51:53,859 --> 00:51:58,137
and, against all odds, he fixed it.

480
00:52:01,066 --> 00:52:04,206
It was the kindest magic trick...

481
00:52:05,637 --> 00:52:07,844
that ever I've seen.

482
00:52:15,981 --> 00:52:20,327
And now, my friends,

483
00:52:20,486 --> 00:52:26,767
I address you all tonight
as you truly are:

484
00:52:26,925 --> 00:52:31,203
Wizards, mermaids...

485
00:52:32,531 --> 00:52:37,913
travelers, adventurers... magicians.

486
00:52:45,377 --> 00:52:49,848
Come and dream with me.

487
00:54:18,937 --> 00:54:24,819
Yes, you can start with the thaumatrope,
the zoetrope, the praxinoscope.

488
00:54:24,977 --> 00:54:27,981
Any study of the history of film
must begin with the...

489
00:54:28,146 --> 00:54:30,524
Poppy? The cave pictographs at...

