00:54:32,317 --> 00:54:35,230
About canine socialization.

492
00:54:35,387 --> 00:54:36,991
Not canine romance?

493
00:54:37,155 --> 00:54:41,001
Oh, Monsieur Frick, do I detect
a pearl in your oyster?

494
00:54:41,159 --> 00:54:44,231
The boy designed it.
It does not squeak at all.

495
00:54:44,930 --> 00:54:46,671
Don't forget to smile, darling.

496
00:54:46,832 --> 00:54:49,472
Well, which one?
I've mastered three of them.

497
00:54:51,403 --> 00:54:55,909
Don't worry. I'm now a fully
functioning man. Aren't I, dear?

498
00:54:56,074 --> 00:55:00,819
Tap the deck. And it's up,
it's up, it's up... It's there!

499
00:55:02,648 --> 00:55:05,060
- Is this your card?
- That is my card.

500
00:55:07,019 --> 00:55:12,697
<i>Once upon</i> a <i>time,
I met</i> a <i>boy named Hugo Cabret.</i>

501
00:55:13,825 --> 00:55:16,772
<i>He lived in a train station.</i>

502
00:55:16,929 --> 00:55:22,504
<i>"Why did he live in a train station?"
you might well ask.</i>

503
00:55:23,368 --> 00:55:26,508
<i>That's really what this hook
